# The World's a Stage


## {Introduction @showdialog}

Let's make a clicker game starring the cast of Sing 2!

![Click away](/static/skillmap/star-sing2/star1.gif "Click and buy bigger clickers" )


## {Step 2}
This game will test your speed as you click quickly as possible to earn points.<br/>
‚≠ê ‚≠ê ‚≠ê


Let's start by setting the stage.

---

- :tree: Open the ``||scene:Scene||`` category and drag<br/>
``||scene: set background image to [ ]||``<br/>
into the ``||loops:on start||``<br/>
container that's already in the workspace.

- :mouse pointer: When you're done, click **Next** to see the next step.


```blocks
//@highlight
scene.setBackgroundImage(img`
. . . .
. . . .
. . . .
. . . .
`)
```


## {Step 3}

**Choose your background!**<br/>
üñº üñº üñº

---


- :paint brush: Click the grey box inside<br/>
``||scene: set background image to [ ]||``<br/>
to open the
image editor and click the **My Assets** tab.

![My Assets](/static/skillmap/assets/my-assets.png "Toggle to see the images for this game" )


- :mouse pointer: Choose the **stage** background and click **Done**.

![The world is a stage](/static/skillmap/star-sing2/stage.png "Find your stage" )




```blocks
//@highlight
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`stage`)
```




## {Step 4}

**Click the Game Window Tab (Above)**<br/>
![Click the Game Window tab to see your scene. ](/static/skillmap/assets/game-win-tab.png "Don't forget to look at your game!")

---

Do you see the background you chose?





## {Step 5}

**Choose your star!**<br/>
‚≠ê ‚≠ê ‚≠ê

Which performer will the audience be cheering for today?<br/>

Do you want to see Buster at the mic, or are you here for Clay Calloway?

---

- :paper plane: From ``||sprites: Sprites||``, drag a<br/>
``||sprites: set [mySprite] to sprite [ ] of kind [Player]||``<br/>
block into **the end** of the ``||loops: on start||`` container.

- :paint brush: Click the empty grey box and toggle to **My Assets** to
 select a character for your project.



```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`stage`)
//@highlight
let mySprite = sprites.create(assets.image`Buster`, SpriteKind.Player)
```





## {Step 6}

Now we need to put our character at their correct place on the stage.

---


- :paper plane: From ``||sprites: Sprites||``, grab<br/>
``||sprites: set [mySprite] [x] to [0]||``<br/>
and snap it into **the end** of the ``||loops: on start||`` container.


- :mouse pointer: To set the bottom of the character to their target spot on the stage,
change ``||sprites:x||`` to ``||sprites:bottom||``.

- :mouse pointer: Change **0** to **115** to move tbe bottom of your character sprite into the spotlight.



```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`stage`)
let mySprite = sprites.create(assets.image`Buster`, SpriteKind.Player)
//@highlight
mySprite.bottom = 115
```




## {Step 7}

**Check your game**<br/>

Switch over to the game window to see how your scene looks so far.

![Click the Game Window tab to see your scene. ](/static/skillmap/assets/game-win-tab.png "Don't forget to look at your game!")


---

You should see your character posing in the spotlight on stage.




## {Step 8}
It's time to add a [__*splash screen*__](#splasht "A full-screen message that shows while a program or level is loading") to let the user know to press the
**‚í∂** button when they're ready to start playing.

---

- :circle: Open the ``||game:Game||`` category and
drag the<br/>
``||game: splash [" "]||``<br/>
block into the bottom of the<br/>
``||loops:on start||`` container.

- :mouse pointer: Click inside the empty text area of the<br/>
``||game: splash [" "]||``<br/>
block and type a message letting the
user know they should press (A) to play.


```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`stage`)
let mySprite = sprites.create(assets.image`Buster`, SpriteKind.Player)
mySprite.bottom = 115
//@highlight
game.splash("Press (A) to play!")

```

## {Step 9}

**‚ö° Here comes the action ‚ö°**

Now the game needs a container to hold the code that
adds to the score when the **‚í∂** button is clicked.

---

- :game: From the ``||controller:Controller||`` category, grab the<br/>
``||controller: on [A] button [pressed]||``<br/>
container and drop it into an
empty spot in the workspace.

- :id card: From ``||info:Info||``, drag out the<br/>
``||info:change score by [1]||``<br/>
block and snap it into<br/>
``||controller: on [A] button [pressed]||``.


```blocks
controller.A.onEvent(ControllerButtonEvent.Pressed, function () {
    info.changeScoreBy(1)
})
```


## {Step 10}

**üéÆ Test your game on the game screen**

Do you see your score go up each time you press the **‚í∂** button?


## {Step 11}

This game is off to a great start...but it goes on forever! Add a countdown timer to give
the player a clear endpoint.

---

- :id card: Open the ``||info:Info||`` category and
drag the<br/>
``||info: start countdown [10] (s)||``<br/>
block into **the bottom** of the<br/>
``||loops:on start||`` container.


```blocks
scene.setBackgroundImage(assets.image`stage`)
let mySprite = sprites.create(assets.image`Buster`, SpriteKind.Player)
mySprite.bottom = 115
game.splash("Press (A) to play!")
//@highlight
info.startCountdown(10)
```


## {Step 12}

**üéâ Congrats üéâ**

You have started your very own clicker game!
Play it on the game screen and see if you can get more than **40 clicks**.

When you're finished, click **Done** to return to the main page where you can share your game with family and friends to compare scores!
